#  Gens Launcher v1.5.0 

This major release brings Gens Launcher to a production-ready state, featuring deep Windows integration, enterprise-grade security patches, and a highly polished user experience.

###  New Features & UX
* **Windows Jump List Integration:** Right-click the app icon in the taskbar to instantly launch your 3 most recently played instances without opening the launcher.
* **Quick Context Menu:** Added a custom right-click menu on instance cards (Launch, Open Folder, Edit, Delete) for faster navigation.
* **Welcome Screen (Empty State):** A new informative and visually appealing welcome screen appears when no instances are installed.
* **UI State Persistence:** The launcher now remembers your category states (collapsed/expanded) between sessions.
* **Professional Installer (NSIS):** Configured `package.json` to compile a professional `.exe` setup file (GensLauncher-Setup) that creates desktop and start menu shortcuts.

###  Security & Anti-Corruption (Major)
* **Safe Write (Anti-Corruption Shield):** Completely rewrote the JSON save system (Instances, Settings, Accounts). It now uses temporary `.tmp` files to make the application invulnerable to PC crashes or power outages during saves.
* **SHA1 Verification:** The launcher now strictly verifies the integrity (SHA1 hash) of mods downloaded from Modrinth to prevent Man-in-the-Middle (MITM) attacks.
* **Strict HTTPS Enforcement:** All mod download requests (CurseForge/Modrinth) are now forced to use secure HTTPS protocols.
* **"Java Trojan" Protection:** The launcher will refuse to execute a custom Java path if it does not strictly point to a valid `java.exe` or `javaw.exe` executable.
* **Path Traversal Filter:** Implemented rigorous filename sanitization (`sanitizeFilename`) to prevent malicious mods from overwriting Windows system files.
* **XSS & DOM Injection Prevention:** Removed raw HTML injections (`innerHTML`) in the icon selector and local server management.
* **Wallpaper Whitelist:** Added a strict file extension whitelist to prevent the importation of executable files disguised as background images.

###  Bug Fixes & Stability
* **Critical:** Fixed an issue where allocated RAM was saved as a `String` instead of a `Number`, preventing silent UI crashes.
* Fixed Toast notification displays when a modpack is only partially created.
* Fixed the Mojang news image domain parser to prevent the loading of unverified third-party domains.

###  Localization (i18n) & Miscellaneous
* **Complete Code Clean-up:** 100% of hardcoded strings have been removed and replaced with the dynamic translation system (`t()`).
* Full English and French support for crash notifications, auto-backups, version incompatibilities, and Discord RPC status.
